.nh
.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-interactive - Start interactive mode with slash commands


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel interactive [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Starts an interactive shell with slash commands for managing your Citadel node.

.PP
Available commands:
  /status    - Show node status dashboard
  /services  - List and manage services
  /logs      - View service logs
  /peers     - Show network peers
  /jobs      - Show job queue status
  /help      - Show available commands
  /quit      - Exit interactive mode


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for interactive


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Start interactive mode
  citadel interactive

  # Or use the short alias
  citadel i
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
